						<summary>

						<p>On a piece of slab built into the north wall of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in the Sōmanātha temple.</p>						

						<p>Circa 12 century.</p>						

						<p>The only details of the date available are Pushya ba. 9, Sunday.</p>						

						<p>It records a gift of land by the two Five Hundred <hi rend="italic">(Mahājanas)</hi> of Iṅgaḷēśvara to the <hi rend="italic">sthānāchārya</hi> Kumāradēva. The earlier portion of the record is lost. </p>						

						</summary>
